





Filt (subroutine)


Entries: filt
Calls  : cos

Purpose:
	Digitally filter a vector using one of a variety of methods.

Limits:
	Finite number of filters, which are not necessarily the best choice.
	Real data only.
	Destroys the input vector.

Arguments:
	Real x(n)		data vector
	Integer n		number of data points
	Integer filtno	filter selection		1 = Hanned filter
								2 = split cosine bell

Usage:
	Determine the type of filter desired; pass the number as filtno.  The remainder of the information necessary will be obtained interactively by the subroutine.  The filtered data will be returned in the input vector.
